-- LLM evaluation:
-- The LLM reads the current prompt ("Summarize this code file and list the key functions")
-- and the weaknesses (no patterns, no relationships, no middleware, not newcomer-useful).
-- It rewrites the вҲҙ to explicitly ask for patterns and relationships.

  yield В§summarize' вүЎ "вҠў summarize\n  given sample-codeвҶ’code\n  yield summary\n\n  вҲҙ Analyze В«sample-codeвҶ’codeВ» for a new developer joining the project.\n    Identify the architectural patterns used (e.g. pub/sub, middleware pipeline,\n    saga). Explain how the classes relate to each other and why each abstraction\n    exists. Describe the data flow through the system.\n\n  вҠЁ summary identifies architectural patterns\n  вҠЁ summary is useful to a new developer"

